        "Community sources now reach Apple TV titles that have no IMDb id. A film or show identified only by a TMDB id was left out of the Singularity community source pool on Apple TV, while the very same title on iPhone was included. Both now resolve their pool identity the same way, so what the community has found is offered on every device. Apple TV.",
        "The diagnostic log you export is cleaned as it is written. Diagnostic logging is off unless you turn it on, and the reason to turn it on is to send the file to us, so the file used to carry what you had been watching and, on a few lines, links holding your own service credentials. Every line is now scrubbed on the way to disk, with a stable stand-in in place of each identifier, so support can still follow one title through the log without the log naming it. Apple TV, iPhone, iPad, and Mac.",
